terms.medium_def:
A man living at the time of Divided Monarchy, first mentioned at 2Ki.22.14; 
referred to as Tikvah (תִּקְוָה), or Tokhath (Qere. Ketiv= Tokahath, KJV= Tikvath) (תּוֹקַהַת); 
a son of Harhas; 
father of Shallum.

A man living at the time of Exile and Return, only mentioned at Ezr.10.15; 
only referred to as Tikvah (תִּקְוָה); 
father of Jahzeiah.

A man living at the time of Divided Monarchy, first mentioned at 2Ki.22.14; 
referred to as Tikvah (תִּקְוָה), or Tokhath (Qere. Ketiv= Tokahath, KJV= Tikvath) (תּוֹקַהַת); 
a son of Harhas; 
father of Shallum. § father of Shallum, the husband of the prophetess Huldah in the time of king Josiah of Judah

A man of the Kingdom of Israel, living at the time of United Monarchy, first mentioned at 1Ki.11.26; 
only referred to as Nebat (נְבָט); 
husband of Zeruah; 
father of Jeroboam. § an Ephraimite of Zereda, father of king Jeroboam I of the northern kingdom of Israel

A man of the Arabs living at the time of the Patriarchs, first mentioned at Gen.25.13; 
only referred to as Nebaioth (נְבָיוֹת); 
son of Ishmael; 
a brother of Kedar, Adbeel, Mibsam, Mishma, Dumah, Massa, Hadad, Tema, Jetur, Naphish, Kedemah and Mahalath.

A man from the tribe of Zebulun living at the time of Egypt and Wilderness, first mentioned at Gen.46.14; 
referred to as Jahleel (יַחְלְאֵל), or Jahleelite (יַחְלְאֵלִי); 
son of Zebulun; 
a brother of Sered and Elon. § the 3rd of the 3 sons of Zebulun; founder of the family of the Jahleelites

A man from the tribe of Zebulun living at the time of Egypt and Wilderness, first mentioned at Gen.46.14; 
referred to as Jahleel (יַחְלְאֵל), or Jahleelite (יַחְלְאֵלִי); 
son of Zebulun; 
a brother of Sered and Elon. § descendants of Jahleel of the tribe of Zebulun

People from Casluch(?) of the Egyptians, first mentioned at Gen.10.14; 
only referred to as Casluhim (כַּסְלֻחִים); 
descended from Egypt along with Ludim, Anamim, Lehabim, Naphtuhim, Pathrusim and Caphtorim; 
progenitors of the Philistine. § a people or tribe descended from Mizraim (Egypt) progenitors of the Philistines and Caphtorim

A man living at the time of Egypt and Wilderness, only mentioned at Num.34.21; 
only referred to as Chislon (כִּסְלוֹן); 
father of Elidad. § father of Elidad, the prince selected to assist in the division of the land of Canaan among the tribes

A man living at the time of Divided Monarchy, first mentioned at 1Ch.16.38; 
only referred to as Hosah (חֹסָה); 
father of Shimri, Hilkiah, Tebaliah, Zechariah.

A man living at the time of Divided Monarchy, first mentioned at Jer.32.12; 
only referred to as Mahseiah (מַחְסֵיָה); 
father of Neriah.

A man from the tribe of Levi living at the time of Divided Monarchy, first mentioned at 1Ch.6.21; 
referred to as Jeatherai (יְאָֽתְרַי), or Ethni (אֶתְנִי); 
a son of Zerah; 
father of Malchijah. § a Gershonite Levite, son of Zerah

A man from the tribe of Judah living at the time of Egypt and Wilderness, first mentioned at Gen.38.5; 
referred to as Shelah (שֵׁלָה), or Shelanite (שֵׁלָנִי); 
son of Judah and Bath-shua; 
a brother of Er and Onan; 
half-brother of: Perez and Zerah; 
father of Er, Laadah, Jokim, Joash and Saraph. § the youngest son of Judah

A man from the tribe of Judah living at the time of Egypt and Wilderness, first mentioned at Gen.38.5; 
referred to as Shelah (שֵׁלָה), or Shelanite (שֵׁלָנִי); 
son of Judah and Bath-shua; 
a brother of Er and Onan; 
half-brother of: Perez and Zerah; 
father of Er, Laadah, Jokim, Joash and Saraph. § Shelanites, of Shelah "quietness"
a descendant of Shelah

A man living at the time of Egypt and Wilderness, first mentioned at Num.1.9; 
only referred to as Helon (חֵלֹן); 
father of Eliab. § father of Eliab of the tribe of Zebulun
